# Global Audit Memory

## Scope Touched
- OpenZeppelin proxy stack: `ERC1967Upgrade`, `ERC1967Proxy`, `TransparentUpgradeableProxy`, `BeaconProxy`, `UpgradeableBeacon`, `Proxy`, `ProxyAdmin` — core attention on upgrade, initialization, admin, and beacon control paths
- Supporting utilities: `Address`, `StorageSlot`, `Ownable`, `IERC1967`, `IERC1822`, `IBeacon` — mainly relevant as helpers enforcing delegatecall, slot, and ownership invariants around the proxy flows
- Deployment/setup flow direction: payable proxy constructors with optional initializer payloads — repeatedly relevant to whether setup delegatecalls execute and how ETH can become stuck at the proxy

## Issue Directions Seen
- Upgrade and initialization sequencing in ERC1967 / transparent / beacon proxy flows remains a central direction, especially around delegatecall-based setup and migration behavior
- Admin-control and storage-slot invariants are a recurring review axis, including `ProxyAdmin` / beacon ownership as the effective upgrade authority surface
- Beacon upgrade paths and transparent proxy admin routing are treated as distinct but related trust/control surfaces
- Payable deployment behavior is a concrete issue direction: proxies can receive ETH during deployment while empty initializer data skips setup execution, creating stranded-funds risk if no recovery route exists
- Ownership transitions such as `renounceOwnership()` on upgrade-control contracts were explored as durable governance-risk context, even when not retained as findings

## Useful Context
- Audit attention has so far concentrated almost entirely on upstream OpenZeppelin proxy infrastructure rather than protocol-specific logic
- Highest scrutiny clustered around proxy entrypoints and upgrade orchestration, with helper libraries read mainly to confirm underlying slot and call semantics
- `Address` and `StorageSlot` matter as supporting context for proxy safety properties but have seen less direct issue-focused attention than upgrade entrypoints
- No cross-agent divergence yet; current memory is shaped by a single review thread focused on upgradeability mechanics and deployment-time fund handling
